This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommendation systems. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for opinionated content modeling, which suggests it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of multi-task learning and tensor factorization techniques indicates it could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the user study aspect of the paper suggests it could also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
